ounting (e.g.userCount).The most common type of loop variable is called acounter, which is a loop variable that counts how many times a loop has executed. In the examples above, the variablecountis a counter.Integral loop variables should be signedIntegral loop variables should almost always be signed, as unsigned integers can lead to unexpected issues. Consider the following code:#include <iostream>

